WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Subtitles By Ra_One

01:24.459 --> 01:34.469
A GENTLE CREATURE

03:23.995 --> 03:26.373
Why are you sitting like this?

03:28.125 --> 03:30.210
Why are you so sad?

05:31.039 --> 05:33.083
I'm talking to you!
Wake up!

05:35.460 --> 05:36.503
Your ID.

05:45.679 --> 05:48.431
Everybody knows.
Everybody understands.

05:48.557 --> 05:51.393
If a war starts, then what?
One nuclear missile...

05:51.518 --> 05:54.062
You think Russians can't aim?

05:54.187 --> 05:59.025
There are many ways
to blow up America with a single missile.

06:00.443 --> 06:04.531
- One nuclear missile, dammit!
- What else is there to say?

06:07.701 --> 06:09.494
Youngsters always
jump the queue.

06:09.619 --> 06:12.455
I need to get my pension.
I want to eat.

06:12.581 --> 06:13.999
Two hundred rubles.

06:14.124 --> 06:15.166
What for?

06:15.709 --> 06:17.043
It's "return to sender".

06:17.168 --> 06:18.461
Why has it been returned?

06:19.296 --> 06:21.464
- Put it over there.
- Doesn't it say anything?

06:22.257 --> 06:24.175
The reason is not specified.

06:24.301 --> 06:25.802
What does that mean?

06:25.927 --> 06:28.013
I don't know.
Where did you send it?

06:29.139 --> 06:31.099
Excuse me.
Do you have any blank forms?

06:31.224 --> 06:32.475
- On the table.
- Thank you.

06:33.143 --> 06:34.269
To a prison?

06:36.938 --> 06:39.107
Sign here.

06:39.232 --> 06:41.359
Doesn't it say anything else?

06:43.570 --> 06:45.071
Are you going to pay?

06:45.864 --> 06:47.490
Or should I take it back?

06:49.492 --> 06:52.537
- Can I collect a parcel?
- There's a queue, young man.

06:54.205 --> 06:56.333
Be patient!

06:57.042 --> 07:00.337
Why has it been returned?
Usually, there are no problems.

07:03.173 --> 07:05.842
Please check.
Isn't there a note?

07:08.178 --> 07:10.138
Maybe it's possible to find out?

07:13.099 --> 07:14.809
Sign here.

07:24.194 --> 07:26.529
Come this way,
I'll give it to you over there.

07:32.994 --> 07:35.330
Maybe there were
some papers attached?

07:35.455 --> 07:38.792
Papers? This is a post office,
not prison information!

07:38.917 --> 07:41.086
Please tell me
who I should contact!

07:42.545 --> 07:43.588
Your husband?

07:46.257 --> 07:47.425
Your son?

07:48.802 --> 07:50.136
Your father, then?

07:50.261 --> 07:51.388
Leave her alone.

07:51.513 --> 07:53.348
Father or no father,
what's it to you?

07:53.473 --> 07:56.935
I'm only trying to help.
Can't you see she is confused?

07:57.060 --> 07:59.646
How can you help her?
Get away from her.

07:59.771 --> 08:01.564
She doesn't want to talk to you.

08:01.690 --> 08:03.358
I'll spit in your face.

08:03.483 --> 08:06.444
I'll cough up some TB on you!

08:06.569 --> 08:08.530
Don't you dare.
Get lost!

09:35.408 --> 09:37.952
Our Zinka. The one who lives
in the blue house.

09:38.078 --> 09:40.163
On the corner of Lenin
and Engels Streets.

09:40.288 --> 09:42.874
They dug up an arm or something
in that area,

09:43.333 --> 09:45.376
and that's where he spotted her.

09:46.920 --> 09:48.004
Which Zinka?

09:48.129 --> 09:50.215
There's only one Zinka round here.

09:52.717 --> 09:54.844
At first they hid the body.

09:55.553 --> 09:56.596
Yes...

09:57.222 --> 10:00.183
I told you!
She knows everything.

10:00.308 --> 10:02.727
Then they went back
and chopped up the body.

10:02.852 --> 10:05.605
With the very same chainsaw
he gave him.

10:05.730 --> 10:08.233
The same chainsaw
they used to cut her up.

10:09.109 --> 10:11.486
Then they buried the parts in the forest,

10:11.611 --> 10:14.697
so the police took a week
to find all the pieces.

10:14.823 --> 10:16.533
Some here, some there.

10:16.658 --> 10:18.785
I wondered why they...

10:19.452 --> 10:21.538
It turns out, that's why.

10:22.664 --> 10:25.750
- They dug it out of the snow?
- No, it was summer.

10:25.875 --> 10:28.169
What am I,
a shelf for your parcel?

10:28.294 --> 10:30.380
Hold your box properly, lady.

10:30.505 --> 10:32.674
Stop putting it on my feet!

10:32.799 --> 10:35.343
I'm wearing stockings, you know.

10:35.468 --> 10:37.137
Get your box off me!

10:37.262 --> 10:39.931
Where should she move it?
There's people here, too!

10:40.056 --> 10:42.392
We have legs, too. Quit moaning!

10:42.517 --> 10:44.185
Mind your own business!

10:44.310 --> 10:46.771
It's not the same.
You're wearing pants.

10:46.896 --> 10:48.731
Pants or no pants,
I still have legs.

10:48.857 --> 10:50.900
They know the bus is packed

10:51.025 --> 10:53.611
and they push inside with their boxes!

10:54.195 --> 10:57.157
They ferry boxes all over the place.

10:57.282 --> 11:01.786
Here, there and back,
boxes all the way!

11:01.911 --> 11:04.873
One time it was a coffin...

11:04.998 --> 11:07.417
The whole bus helped to hold it.

11:07.542 --> 11:10.336
They held it high, over their heads.

11:10.461 --> 11:11.796
What choice did they have?

11:11.921 --> 11:14.757
A man died. He must be buried.

11:14.883 --> 11:16.759
His relatives could pay
for a coffin,

11:16.885 --> 11:19.012
but not for transportation.

11:19.137 --> 11:20.930
So they had to take it on the bus.

11:21.055 --> 11:23.766
Who would object?
Nobody.

11:23.892 --> 11:25.685
We're all going to die.

11:27.353 --> 11:33.067
So, your coffin, clear lady,
will be carried in the same manner.

11:33.193 --> 11:35.195
Shut up, old lady!

11:35.320 --> 11:37.530
Why?
You think you're immortal?

11:37.655 --> 11:39.490
We're all going to croak.
Even you.

11:39.616 --> 11:43.453
And you won't need your stockings, then.

11:43.953 --> 11:46.414
Just my luck...

11:46.539 --> 11:51.002
Every time I get on a bus,
there's always some idiot riding with me!

11:51.461 --> 11:54.088
Who won't shut up!

11:54.214 --> 11:56.758
Now she doesn't like my stockings.

11:56.883 --> 11:59.427
Know where you can shove
my stockings?

11:59.552 --> 12:02.305
I had a pal about 20 years ago.

12:02.430 --> 12:06.226
One night we ride the bus home.
The next day he doesn't turn up.

12:06.351 --> 12:08.728
What happened?
He died overnight.

12:08.853 --> 12:09.979
Just like that.

12:11.689 --> 12:13.441
The detective kept coming.

12:13.566 --> 12:17.070
They'd dug everything up
and ID'd the body.

12:17.195 --> 12:19.781
But he kept coming back.

12:19.906 --> 12:24.285
So the people started wondering,
why is he still hanging around?

12:26.162 --> 12:30.083
He wasn't getting anywhere.
Just kept coming and going.

12:30.208 --> 12:31.334
So?

12:31.459 --> 12:34.170
So I'm telling you.
He was visiting Zinka.

12:34.295 --> 12:37.548
While looking for the corpse,
he had his eye on Zinka.

12:37.674 --> 12:40.218
- And?
- Our Zinka.

12:40.343 --> 12:43.763
The one in the blue house,
at the corner of Lenin and Engels.

12:43.888 --> 12:48.351
They dug up an arm or something
and he chatted her up...

16:49.383 --> 16:52.762
I've been looking out for you!
I wasn't sure that was you.

16:53.638 --> 16:57.934
My nephew is here.
I filled his tank from our extra supply.

16:58.059 --> 17:01.103
It's too far to walk.
The roads are bad.

17:01.229 --> 17:02.980
- Say hello.
- Hi.

17:05.942 --> 17:09.694
If Petrovich drops by,
tell him that the pump is leaking.

17:09.819 --> 17:11.989
I told him already,
but he didn't fix it.

17:16.618 --> 17:17.869
Oh Well...

17:18.746 --> 17:23.584
There's water, tea and sugar.

17:23.709 --> 17:26.378
And there's some bread left.
Help yourself.

17:26.837 --> 17:27.922
Well...

17:29.674 --> 17:32.426
The lock is on the nail,
the key is in the lock.

17:32.552 --> 17:34.679
I'm off, over to you.

17:36.806 --> 17:41.602
You won't be bored tonight,
you've got company.

17:42.853 --> 17:45.565
What's worth guarding
in your house?

17:45.690 --> 17:48.484
Can you replace me next week?

17:49.610 --> 17:51.028
Something happened?

17:52.321 --> 17:55.157
They granted me a visit.
I need a couple of days.

17:57.910 --> 18:01.122
This is sacred.
You'll see your man.

18:01.247 --> 18:02.873
You're withering away,
here alone.

18:05.126 --> 18:06.377
Be quiet!

18:06.502 --> 18:08.045
Is it OK?

18:08.546 --> 18:11.424
So you get to go to town.

18:12.216 --> 18:13.926
You get to see people.

18:16.721 --> 18:20.433
My man never went to prison,

18:20.558 --> 18:23.269
so I never had a chance
to see the world.

18:25.813 --> 18:27.815
Oh God...
Son of a bitch!

18:27.940 --> 18:30.901
I hope they put him in prison one day.

18:31.027 --> 18:32.737
Can you cover for me?

18:32.862 --> 18:33.904
Well...

18:35.740 --> 18:38.784
You stay here all clay long,
not a single car.

18:38.909 --> 18:42.955
Nobody to talk to.
What are we guarding here?

18:43.623 --> 18:48.586
There was just one car today.
A foreigner. Spoke no Russian.

18:48.711 --> 18:54.383
I say this, I say that,
all he can say is "bla-bla-bla".

18:55.134 --> 18:58.512
And you're going to town!
You're going to see people!

18:58.638 --> 19:02.350
We're stuck here with the radio,
nothing but "bla-bla-bla".

19:02.475 --> 19:04.393
So? Is it OK then?

19:05.269 --> 19:08.314
I have to go.
He's waiting for me.

19:08.439 --> 19:09.857
What's your answer?

19:12.526 --> 19:14.195
My answer, my answer...

19:15.071 --> 19:16.781
Bring us a treat.

19:17.698 --> 19:20.076
Not for me. I need nothing.

19:20.201 --> 19:22.703
Something for my nephew.
He's got a sweet tooth.

19:23.829 --> 19:25.665
I'll leave the dog here.

19:26.415 --> 19:27.500
Look after the house.

19:27.625 --> 19:30.586
You've got nothing to steal!

19:32.797 --> 19:34.590
Off we go!

20:30.479 --> 20:32.356
Step through.

20:43.367 --> 20:45.619
Through the metal detector.

20:46.245 --> 20:47.872
Hurry UP-

21:02.261 --> 21:04.013
Step on through.

21:04.138 --> 21:07.057
Keys, phones and weapons on the table!
Keep it moving.

21:07.183 --> 21:09.560
And the weapon between my legs?
On the table, too?

21:09.685 --> 21:11.771
There's always castration.

21:11.896 --> 21:14.106
It's not castration,
it's circumcision!

21:14.231 --> 21:16.734
- Over here, with your bag.
- Move on.

21:17.568 --> 21:18.861
For kids?

21:18.986 --> 21:20.863
Yes, kids' stuff, and mine.

21:29.497 --> 21:30.998
Move on.

21:33.959 --> 21:35.419
What have you got in here?

21:36.545 --> 21:37.880
A box.

21:38.005 --> 21:39.340
What kind of box?

21:39.799 --> 21:40.966
A parcel.

21:42.092 --> 21:43.552
What kind of parcel?

21:43.677 --> 21:45.429
An ordinary parcel.

21:45.888 --> 21:47.473
And what's in the parcel?

21:47.598 --> 21:50.351
Some things, clothes,
canned food.

21:50.476 --> 21:51.852
What canned food?

21:52.478 --> 21:53.771
Canned fish.

21:55.022 --> 21:56.065
I see.

21:56.732 --> 21:58.651
Take your bag and follow me.

22:09.161 --> 22:11.622
- Where are you going?
- Siberia, of course.

22:11.747 --> 22:13.999
- Excellent choice of destination!
- Thanks.

22:39.483 --> 22:42.069
- What's that?
- Condensed milk.

22:42.194 --> 22:43.737
Are you sure?

22:44.947 --> 22:46.365
You can check it.

22:46.490 --> 22:47.825
Want some condensed milk?

22:49.493 --> 22:53.330
Boss, I want
some condensed milk!

22:55.624 --> 22:57.209
Meanie!

23:00.880 --> 23:02.423
Give me some condensed milk!

23:03.507 --> 23:05.426
Put that back.

23:05.885 --> 23:07.887
Put it all back in. Hurry up.

23:09.138 --> 23:10.681
Don't do it!

23:11.557 --> 23:14.518
Girl, give me some condensed milk,
please.

23:15.352 --> 23:16.729
Baby!

23:19.148 --> 23:20.274
Don't be mean!

23:20.399 --> 23:21.483
Stop.

23:21.984 --> 23:23.110
Take your coat off.

23:23.694 --> 23:24.904
Take it off.

23:26.572 --> 23:27.656
Strip her!

23:27.781 --> 23:29.366
Against the wall. Arms up.

23:29.491 --> 23:32.202
Hey red-dress, how do you do?
How about a little screw?

23:33.537 --> 23:35.372
What a pretty girl!

23:36.332 --> 23:37.583
Do you like her?

23:37.708 --> 23:38.959
Turn round.

23:39.501 --> 23:41.045
Touch me!

23:41.837 --> 23:43.339
Touch me up!

23:43.923 --> 23:45.841
Touch me up, boss!

23:48.218 --> 23:50.179
Get dressed and take your stuff.

23:52.806 --> 23:55.476
Why get dressed?
Get undressed!

23:57.353 --> 23:58.812
Get undressed!

24:00.356 --> 24:01.398
Boss...

24:02.358 --> 24:03.692
Undress her!

24:05.361 --> 24:07.154
What's your husband in prison for?

24:08.364 --> 24:10.115
Murder.

24:10.240 --> 24:11.492
Of a cat!

24:11.992 --> 24:14.453
- Who did he kill?
- Give me condensed milk!

24:14.578 --> 24:15.621
Nobody.

24:16.622 --> 24:18.707
- So why is he in prison?
- He killed a cat!

24:20.000 --> 24:21.710
Because he was sentenced.

24:22.419 --> 24:24.129
It can happen to anyone.

24:25.339 --> 24:27.174
You don't go to prison
for nothing, here.

24:27.299 --> 24:29.051
Nonsense.

24:29.677 --> 24:30.970
Yes, you do!

24:31.095 --> 24:32.554
Why am I in prison?

24:33.514 --> 24:36.058
I love women
and I want condensed milk!

24:37.142 --> 24:40.270
Should I go to prison for that?
Because I want milk?

24:40.396 --> 24:45.275
Citizen X was questioned
by Officers Y and Z

24:45.401 --> 24:49.571
on this date, of that year,
at the entrance to N town station,

24:49.697 --> 24:50.948
on suspicion of terrorism.

24:51.073 --> 24:53.409
Citizen X was searched,
nothing found.

24:53.534 --> 24:59.665
Citizen X was then released
to continue her journey to prison X

25:00.207 --> 25:02.918
for the purpose
of visiting her husband.

25:07.756 --> 25:09.842
- Sign and date it.
- Sign nothing!

25:09.967 --> 25:11.010
What is this for?

25:11.468 --> 25:14.221
Rules.
What do you think?

25:14.346 --> 25:15.472
Don't sign!

25:15.597 --> 25:17.558
Sign and you can go.

25:18.225 --> 25:20.144
Say you're illiterate.

25:22.479 --> 25:23.939
Put her in here!

25:25.190 --> 25:27.151
I'll beat the shit out of you, freak!

25:28.027 --> 25:30.154
Easy to pick on a cripple!

25:32.281 --> 25:33.699
Give me milk!

25:33.824 --> 25:37.244
And all the shit fell on our country.
Yanks and fucking Nazis.

25:37.786 --> 25:40.289
- Are you nuts?
- You guys fucked up.

25:40.414 --> 25:42.916
You weren't born,
when I drove a tank.

25:43.042 --> 25:44.251
Know what that means?

25:44.376 --> 25:46.545
It was great.
The whole world in our hand.

25:46.670 --> 25:49.423
Lady, do you know what that means?

25:49.548 --> 25:51.717
Your generation fucked it all up!

25:51.842 --> 25:54.344
What about you?
Do you know about our tanks?

25:55.054 --> 25:58.140
<i>The armour is strong
and our tanks are swift!</i>

25:58.265 --> 25:59.308
There!

25:59.433 --> 26:02.519
<i>And our men are full of courage</i>

26:02.644 --> 26:06.565
<i>The Soviet tankmen are
ready for action</i>

26:06.690 --> 26:10.486
<i>Sons of their Great Motherland!</i>

26:10.611 --> 26:14.448
<i>Thundering with fire,
steel gleaming in the sun</i>

26:14.573 --> 26:18.077
<i>The tanks will launch
a mighty attack!</i>

26:18.202 --> 26:21.789
<i>When we're called to battle
by Comrade Stalin</i>

26:21.914 --> 26:24.500
<i>Voroshilov will lead us all the way!</i>

26:24.625 --> 26:27.544
Exactly! Squash the fuckers.
Our grandfathers weren't dumb!

26:27.669 --> 26:30.923
They knew what they were doing
when they built all that.

26:31.048 --> 26:32.091
That's it.

26:33.425 --> 26:35.594
Drink to that with us, lady!

26:35.719 --> 26:38.806
Let's drink to your son.
May he rest in peace.

26:40.390 --> 26:43.727
To your son, lady!
You must drink to this, it's sacred!

26:47.064 --> 26:48.482
Rest in peace.

26:48.607 --> 26:50.567
May he rest in peace.
To your son.

26:59.535 --> 27:01.578
Well clone, lady.

27:11.088 --> 27:13.048
I got home from work,

27:13.674 --> 27:15.926
and found a note,
saying to go somewhere.

27:16.051 --> 27:17.302
I went.

27:19.221 --> 27:22.683
And they told me:
"here's the address, off you go."

27:23.892 --> 27:26.228
They tell me there's been
a tragedy, a heroic death.

27:27.646 --> 27:30.149
They said I should sign
the papers to get the money.

27:32.568 --> 27:34.403
I couldn't understand it,

27:34.528 --> 27:37.030
but they said
they'd take care of everything.

27:38.323 --> 27:40.617
They said: "go pick it up."

27:41.201 --> 27:42.828
But what?

27:45.038 --> 27:47.082
So I went. What else could I do?

27:49.126 --> 27:52.129
It took me a whole day
to find a replacement.

27:52.588 --> 27:55.090
I had to or they'd fire me.
And then what?

27:56.884 --> 27:59.178
They said that...

28:03.515 --> 28:05.225
"For your dead son,

28:06.643 --> 28:09.229
you'll get a lot of money."

28:10.189 --> 28:12.566
What money?
How will they pay me?

28:13.817 --> 28:14.985
So here I am.

28:17.362 --> 28:19.865
Pick what up?
My son or the money?

28:21.491 --> 28:24.828
So where was he killed?

28:26.914 --> 28:28.081
Lady?

28:29.166 --> 28:32.252
Did they tell you where he was killed?

28:40.969 --> 28:42.596
They didn't tell me where...

28:42.721 --> 28:45.224
The guy was a hero.

28:45.349 --> 28:47.017
- To the hero!
- To the hero!

28:47.601 --> 28:48.810
May he rest in peace.

29:05.619 --> 29:10.249
<i>Over the river Don,
under a large oak</i>

29:10.374 --> 29:14.169
<i>A Cossack woman waved goodbye
to her handsome bloke</i>

29:18.799 --> 29:23.303
<i>A Cossack woman waved goodbye
to her handsome bloke</i>

29:23.428 --> 29:27.808
<i>She waved goodbye by the town
of Rostov, in a field</i>

29:27.933 --> 29:32.479
<i>She embraced her dashing
Cossack in the blowing wind</i>

29:38.568 --> 29:40.570
I grew up in Magadan, Siberia.

29:41.613 --> 29:43.490
We can beat them all!

29:43.615 --> 29:45.575
We will, man, we will.

29:45.701 --> 29:49.121
The whole world is looking at us!
We're doing this for them!

29:49.246 --> 29:50.914
I grew up in Magadan.

29:51.456 --> 29:53.083
So many people died!

29:53.208 --> 29:56.670
We sacrifice everything,
but they are all against us!

29:58.422 --> 29:59.464
Why?

29:59.589 --> 30:02.592
Because they're all
a bunch of assholes, man.

30:03.093 --> 30:05.095
Why should we save them?

30:05.220 --> 30:07.347
It's our mission, to save the world.

30:07.472 --> 30:09.766
That's exactly what I mean!
Mission!

30:10.225 --> 30:13.770
When I was a kid,
there were rockets all over town.

30:13.895 --> 30:17.566
But they let it all go,
and the world got ugly.

30:18.317 --> 30:23.572
So now they are making rockets again,
so no one can push us about.

30:23.697 --> 30:26.033
Do you have your own mug,
my friend?

30:35.709 --> 30:37.669
Let's drink to our great mission!

30:37.794 --> 30:39.796
To our enormous suffering.

30:39.921 --> 30:41.423
- To our guys!
- To our guys!

30:45.177 --> 30:46.470
You want some tea?

30:55.687 --> 30:58.523
- Tea? Tea, anyone?
- Thanks.

30:58.648 --> 31:00.400
- How much?
- 20 rubles.

31:00.901 --> 31:02.027
No, thanks.

31:02.861 --> 31:04.529
Put one glass there!

31:04.654 --> 31:06.114
It's on me, my sweet.

31:07.699 --> 31:09.034
My sweet...

31:11.244 --> 31:12.371
Thank you.

31:13.914 --> 31:15.248
Where are you going?

31:15.749 --> 31:17.334
To visit my husband.

31:18.085 --> 31:19.294
What's he in for?

31:20.295 --> 31:21.338
For nothing.

31:22.839 --> 31:24.508
So what was he sentenced for?

31:25.550 --> 31:26.927
Nothing.

31:27.552 --> 31:29.346
They put him in, he'll get out.

31:29.471 --> 31:32.682
I did 5 years.
I still don't know why.

31:32.808 --> 31:34.559
That's what prison's like.

31:39.606 --> 31:45.028
<i>I remember the port of Vanino</i>

31:46.029 --> 31:51.785
<i>The ominous cry of the steamships</i>

31:52.285 --> 31:57.582
<i>As we climbed a ladder to board</i>

31:58.667 --> 32:03.964
<i>To descend into cold dark holds</i>

32:04.714 --> 32:10.095
<i>The swell tormented us prisoners</i>

32:10.220 --> 32:16.059
<i>As we clung to each other like brothers</i>

32:16.601 --> 32:21.648
<i>And, now and then, bitter curses</i>

32:22.482 --> 32:27.988
<i>Escaped our suffering lips</i>

32:29.239 --> 32:34.786
<i>The mist disappeared by day</i>

32:36.121 --> 32:41.918
<i>The violent storm had subsided</i>

32:42.461 --> 32:48.341
<i>The great Magadan came our way</i>

32:49.468 --> 32:55.474
<i>The heart of the land of Kolyma</i>

32:56.683 --> 33:02.105
<i>I know you're not waiting for me</i>

33:02.981 --> 33:08.904
<i>And you don't even open my letters</i>

33:09.905 --> 33:15.994
<i>You will never come to meet me</i>

33:16.661 --> 33:22.876
<i>And even if you do, you won't know me</i>

34:02.082 --> 34:04.125
Going somewhere?

34:06.628 --> 34:08.838
Go on, go on, give me your bag.

34:30.944 --> 34:32.696
What are you waiting for?
Get in.

34:32.821 --> 34:34.989
I'm the cheapest here.

35:25.957 --> 35:27.500
Where are you going?

35:29.085 --> 35:30.879
Where do you think?

35:31.379 --> 35:34.799
Either a hotel or the prison.
Which do you like better?

35:34.924 --> 35:36.176
I need to go to the prison.

35:36.301 --> 35:38.011
That's what I thought.

35:41.723 --> 35:42.849
Husband?

35:44.517 --> 35:45.560
Father?

35:46.853 --> 35:48.021
Is it your son?

35:48.980 --> 35:50.482
Just someone I know.

35:51.691 --> 35:53.610
I see... Well, well.

35:53.735 --> 35:55.070
It's a date, isn't it?

35:55.654 --> 35:56.863
Something like that.

35:59.824 --> 36:03.119
I've seen a lot of your kind.

36:03.244 --> 36:06.247
Some real stunners!
Sweep you off your feet.

36:06.373 --> 36:09.042
I remember one black girl.
One hot mama!

36:09.167 --> 36:10.794
Great big lips she had.

36:10.919 --> 36:12.671
And everything else, too.

36:13.672 --> 36:15.131
Is this your first time?

36:16.925 --> 36:19.552
You behave like a fresher.
I could tell.

36:20.095 --> 36:21.930
You look at people differently.

36:22.597 --> 36:26.309
Nobody looks you in the eye
here, just the odd glance.

36:26.434 --> 36:27.727
Guess why?

36:27.852 --> 36:30.897
You got it.
Man is a wolf to his fellow man.

36:31.022 --> 36:34.275
And how do wolves live?
In packs. Get it?

36:35.276 --> 36:37.320
Our prison here is
a sacred place.

36:37.445 --> 36:39.948
An icon. It made this town.

36:40.448 --> 36:42.283
What would you do here
without a prison?

36:42.867 --> 36:45.537
It's as precious as gold.

36:46.037 --> 36:47.747
It helps people live.

36:48.289 --> 36:53.002
Some people stay inside,
and others live off it.

36:53.128 --> 36:55.171
You get it?
There.

36:55.672 --> 36:58.007
So here we pray for this prison
to thrive and prosper.

36:58.133 --> 37:01.136
It's our church, so to speak.

37:01.720 --> 37:04.931
People like you come,
I earn a living.

37:05.056 --> 37:07.600
I give you a lift, some food,
here and there,

37:07.726 --> 37:09.477
that's how the economy works.

37:10.145 --> 37:11.646
And what's prison?

37:12.397 --> 37:14.274
It keeps people safe.

37:14.399 --> 37:16.693
People are brainless creatures.

37:17.235 --> 37:20.572
Let them out, they get shot.
End of story.

37:20.697 --> 37:22.407
But in prison it's like
they're in a bank vault.

37:22.907 --> 37:27.078
You do your time, you pay,
you get out. Sign here!

37:27.203 --> 37:29.372
Want to stay longer?
By all means!

37:29.914 --> 37:32.876
You get out,
breathe the air of freedom,

37:33.001 --> 37:35.628
look at the blue sky,
hang out with your mates,

37:35.754 --> 37:37.505
have a great time...

37:38.757 --> 37:40.800
...and then you get low.

37:40.925 --> 37:43.136
Sick with depression.

37:43.762 --> 37:45.221
It's so bad you could choke.

37:46.222 --> 37:48.558
The prison saved so many people.

37:49.017 --> 37:52.479
You can't imagine who's been here.

37:52.604 --> 37:54.189
So your man's lucky.

37:54.314 --> 37:55.774
We've got a great prison.

37:58.067 --> 37:59.819
We'll be there in a sec.

37:59.944 --> 38:03.072
I'll drive you up right there,
like a VIP.

38:16.044 --> 38:18.797
- Where do I go now?
- You walk.

38:18.922 --> 38:20.465
Where to?

38:20.590 --> 38:24.177
I'm not allowed any closer.
I drove you as far as I could.

38:25.386 --> 38:27.013
The office is over there.

39:06.386 --> 39:08.680
Fill out two copies.

39:08.805 --> 39:11.683
They also eat snails
in that shitty France.

39:11.808 --> 39:14.185
Snails squeak when you eat them.
Savages!

39:14.310 --> 39:15.979
- Next!
- Two forms, please.

39:16.104 --> 39:17.313
40 rubles.

39:21.109 --> 39:23.987
And why is your nose all burnt?
Don't you use sunscreen?

39:24.904 --> 39:26.781
Fill out two copies.

39:26.906 --> 39:28.116
Next!

39:28.241 --> 39:30.285
Next!
Can't you talk?

39:36.040 --> 39:37.750
Fill out two copies.

39:38.877 --> 39:42.922
A guy had 3 sons,
2 in prison, one moron.

39:43.047 --> 39:46.259
They pick one
and give him hell.

39:47.719 --> 39:48.761
Next!

39:48.887 --> 39:51.222
If he puts up a fight
they beat him up.

39:51.347 --> 39:53.600
They make threats to tear him
limb from limb

39:53.725 --> 39:57.896
until he looks like
the Union Jack!

39:58.646 --> 40:03.192
Until he remembers the criminal code
and his crimes.

40:03.318 --> 40:04.986
That's how it works...

40:05.111 --> 40:06.154
Next!

40:06.821 --> 40:09.574
So I'm telling you.
This joint is OK.

40:10.867 --> 40:12.994
Parcels get inside,
all nice and legal.

40:13.453 --> 40:15.663
Some say
the army recruits in here.

40:15.788 --> 40:18.833
A reduced sentence in exchange
for combat duty.

40:18.958 --> 40:21.377
It's all lies made up in America.

40:21.502 --> 40:24.047
Who'd agree
to get themselves killed?

40:24.172 --> 40:27.133
That's what I've heard.
I don't know myself.

40:27.926 --> 40:30.553
- It has to be official, right?
- All done in secret.

40:30.678 --> 40:33.723
One day he's a prison inmate,
and the next day,

40:33.848 --> 40:35.892
he's a hero
of the Russian Federation.

40:36.351 --> 40:38.519
He gets a flat, a car, the whole lot.

40:38.645 --> 40:41.731
Serve your motherland,
your motherland covers you.

40:41.856 --> 40:43.524
Hero my ass.

40:43.650 --> 40:45.234
They snuff him out.

40:45.360 --> 40:47.278
Never trust cops, or the army.

40:47.403 --> 40:48.947
Don't sell us this crap.

40:49.072 --> 40:51.449
Did you bring a parcel
or you're just keeping warm?

40:51.574 --> 40:53.034
- It's not allowed.
- Bothering people!

40:53.159 --> 40:56.162
Why isn't it allowed?

40:56.287 --> 40:57.580
I can show you a receipt.

40:57.705 --> 40:59.832
It's Krakow sausage!
Kra-kow.

40:59.958 --> 41:01.960
Can you believe it?

41:02.085 --> 41:04.420
They're not accepting
smoked sausage today!

41:04.545 --> 41:07.298
- Next!
- They make up new rules every day!

41:16.307 --> 41:17.558
Sign here.

41:28.277 --> 41:29.696
Next.

41:37.036 --> 41:38.454
Your papers.

41:42.375 --> 41:43.418
Not allowed.

41:43.543 --> 41:46.295
How come?
It's on the list!

41:47.296 --> 41:48.673
OK, get it out.

41:49.507 --> 41:51.968
Does your husband get
his meat out, too?

41:52.093 --> 41:54.012
Yeah, I doubt
you have a husband...

42:10.862 --> 42:12.196
Not allowed.

42:12.321 --> 42:14.032
What is allowed here?

42:14.157 --> 42:16.325
You don't eat anything
and you don't let others?

42:16.451 --> 42:18.995
- Come on.
- People need to eat.

42:27.503 --> 42:30.256
If I had known,
I'd have brought cheap cigs.

42:32.175 --> 42:34.719
Like the crap you smoke.

42:41.100 --> 42:43.019
How's anyone going
to shave with those?

42:43.936 --> 42:46.564
Take one,
you could slit your wrists.

42:46.689 --> 42:47.774
Shut up.

42:47.899 --> 42:49.901
Don't shut me up!

42:50.026 --> 42:52.904
You didn't open my mouth,
and you can't shut it.

42:57.533 --> 42:59.911
Relax!
What the hell is this mess?

43:04.540 --> 43:06.417
Those were good slippers!

43:08.461 --> 43:11.506
I bet you've never seen
anything like them.

43:12.006 --> 43:13.758
You and your felt boots...

43:13.883 --> 43:14.967
And...

43:17.970 --> 43:20.181
You can have them now.

43:21.474 --> 43:24.102
Take them to your grave.

43:25.394 --> 43:27.563
Something to tart you up in there.

43:27.688 --> 43:29.232
The conversation is over.

43:29.357 --> 43:31.859
It hasn't even started.

43:34.987 --> 43:36.906
I'll see you soon, skank.

43:37.031 --> 43:38.449
Shut your trap.

43:38.574 --> 43:39.742
Next.

43:43.704 --> 43:44.831
Your papers?

44:04.433 --> 44:05.518
Next.

44:05.977 --> 44:08.729
- Why next? What about me?
- Not allowed. Next!

44:08.855 --> 44:13.151
- Why?
- Because I said so.

44:13.276 --> 44:15.528
And don't make a fuss.
Next!

44:15.653 --> 44:17.530
Check the files!
Is my husband here?

44:17.655 --> 44:19.031
Can you tell me where he is?

44:19.157 --> 44:22.702
You need to file an enquiry,
with the appropriate department.

44:22.827 --> 44:24.120
Next!
I'm no information desk.

44:24.245 --> 44:26.831
But why do you refuse my parcel?

44:26.956 --> 44:29.041
I've had enough.

44:29.167 --> 44:31.794
I'm not obliged to do anything!

44:33.004 --> 44:35.965
What was the point of that?
Now we all suffer!

44:36.090 --> 44:38.968
Talk bad to them and they get ratty.

44:39.093 --> 44:40.511
They're already rats.

44:40.636 --> 44:44.015
Don't shout at the woman.
You can see she's upset...

44:44.140 --> 44:45.725
We are all upset!

44:45.850 --> 44:48.519
Don't worry, lady,
it'll be OK.

44:48.978 --> 44:51.689
- The bitch is crabby today, that's all.
- Yes, of course.

45:00.865 --> 45:03.826
I feel sorry anyway...
For all of us.

45:37.318 --> 45:38.569
Do you smoke?

45:39.987 --> 45:41.781
Then I won't either.

45:43.574 --> 45:45.243
So they didn't accept it.

45:46.869 --> 45:48.704
It happens quite often here.

45:49.455 --> 45:51.415
Don't be upset.
You'll come back tomorrow.

45:52.625 --> 45:54.126
Do you have a place to stay?

45:55.419 --> 45:56.754
I don't know, yet.

45:57.713 --> 46:00.549
OK, look here,
there is a hotel in town,

46:01.008 --> 46:05.137
but it's for big fraudsters,
money hustlers.

46:05.263 --> 46:07.098
The ones with dough.

46:08.474 --> 46:10.601
The others rent rooms in town.

46:11.602 --> 46:13.271
My name is Zinka.

46:14.480 --> 46:16.065
I won't charge you much.

46:17.775 --> 46:19.068
I'm doing it for the people,

46:19.193 --> 46:21.779
because I want to help
the likes of you.

46:23.281 --> 46:26.117
People like you suffer so much,
so much...

46:27.326 --> 46:30.079
It breaks my heart.

46:31.747 --> 46:33.624
I have a room for you.

46:34.166 --> 46:37.044
Better than a hen house.
But you'll have to share.

46:37.169 --> 46:38.754
People in the same situation.

46:39.588 --> 46:41.173
Do you think you are unique?

46:43.175 --> 46:46.470
It's small but cosy.
Nothing fancy.

46:46.595 --> 46:47.847
Shall we go?

46:47.972 --> 46:49.181
Let's go!

46:49.307 --> 46:51.225
You must be hungry.

47:00.651 --> 47:03.821
This one's fast,
always gets her prey.

47:05.364 --> 47:06.866
Lots of suckers around.

47:12.496 --> 47:13.789
<i>Alyonka!</i>

47:13.914 --> 47:16.917
<i>She's still soaking
on the platform in the rain</i>

47:17.043 --> 47:18.294
More booze?

47:18.419 --> 47:21.797
<i>Farewell, farewell,
my clear soulmate</i>

47:22.256 --> 47:25.051
<i>I'll never see my love again</i>

47:26.302 --> 47:30.014
<i>The mill of life will grind up everything</i>

47:30.139 --> 47:33.142
<i>That got mixed up in our way</i>

47:34.101 --> 47:37.521
<i>Let tears flow like a fountain</i>

47:38.147 --> 47:41.150
<i>From your lovely big eyes</i>

47:41.901 --> 47:45.654
<i>My dear friend is now out of here</i>

47:45.780 --> 47:47.990
<i>She goes back to normal life</i>

47:48.115 --> 47:52.078
<i>And the freedom,
and the freedom tastes so good</i>

47:52.203 --> 47:55.623
<i>Mum and Dad, I don't doubt,
wait for you</i>

47:56.415 --> 47:59.627
<i>And your darling baby sister...</i>

47:59.752 --> 48:01.587
<i>Alyonka!</i>

48:01.712 --> 48:05.216
<i>She's still soaking
on the platform in the rain</i>

48:06.342 --> 48:10.054
<i>Farewell, farewell,
our paths are parting</i>

48:10.179 --> 48:13.057
<i>And our fate is split in two</i>

48:14.266 --> 48:17.561
<i>You will be fighting for your future</i>

48:18.312 --> 48:21.565
<i>I will be rotting in my cell</i>

48:22.149 --> 48:25.694
<i>Let tears flow like a fountain</i>

48:26.237 --> 48:28.989
<i>Forcing the guards to look away</i>

48:29.949 --> 48:33.619
<i>It'll always stay in our memory</i>

48:33.744 --> 48:35.996
<i>The scroll of Shakhov prison days</i>

48:36.122 --> 48:39.625
<i>And the freedom,
and the freedom tastes so good</i>

48:39.750 --> 48:43.671
<i>Mum and Dad, I don't doubt,
wait for you</i>

48:43.796 --> 48:46.132
<i>And your darling baby sister...</i>

48:46.257 --> 48:48.592
Hush! What's her name?

48:48.717 --> 48:50.177
What's her name? Come on!

48:50.719 --> 48:52.471
Come on! Say it!

48:53.097 --> 48:54.140
Alyonka?

48:54.265 --> 48:56.308
<i>Alyonka!</i>

48:56.434 --> 48:59.854
<i>She's waiting for your train
in the pouring rain</i>

49:00.479 --> 49:01.522
Mum!

49:12.658 --> 49:13.993
Bravo!

49:17.455 --> 49:19.832
<i>Let's drink to Ra ya,
our young Ra ya!</i>

49:19.957 --> 49:24.170
<i>The world hasn't seen
a drunkard like her!</i>

49:24.295 --> 49:28.549
<i>Raya, Raya, bottoms up!
We will fill another cup!</i>

49:28.674 --> 49:32.470
<i>Raya, Raya, bottoms up!
We will fill another cup!</i>

49:36.056 --> 49:40.519
When I worked for a newspaper,

49:41.270 --> 49:44.273
I wrote children's poetry,
poetry as if written by children.

49:44.398 --> 49:47.193
- Lard?
- Gherkins sitting in a jar.

49:47.776 --> 49:49.612
- Juicy, tasty as they are.
- Yes, yes.

49:49.737 --> 49:52.823
"Days and weeks go by,
Life is tough for little guys.

49:52.948 --> 49:55.576
"If the jar doesn't explode,
they will meet their end alone!"

49:55.701 --> 49:57.119
Dumb pickles!

49:57.244 --> 50:00.539
Hang on,
don't interrupt, there's more.

50:00.664 --> 50:04.710
"Couldn't wait another day,
pushed the lid off far away!

50:04.835 --> 50:06.670
"Seal the jar, it lasts for years.

50:06.795 --> 50:09.173
"Now the housewife's in tears."

50:09.798 --> 50:12.843
- I know a joke about cucumbers.
- Hang on, I'm not finished.

50:12.968 --> 50:15.513
That poem cost me my job!

50:15.638 --> 50:17.014
One day the boss says to me,

50:18.766 --> 50:19.808
"Did you Write this?"

50:23.604 --> 50:25.689
I foolishly thought
he would give me a raise,

50:25.814 --> 50:28.442
but they sacked me
for political propaganda.

50:29.026 --> 50:32.530
- They said my poem incited revolt.
- What fucking nonsense!

50:33.739 --> 50:34.907
Want one?

50:35.032 --> 50:37.576
Listen, guys,
I know a joke about cucumbers.

50:38.244 --> 50:40.788
A woman asks her neighbour,

50:40.913 --> 50:43.832
"How come your tomatoes grow so well?"

50:43.958 --> 50:47.336
And the neighbour says,
"I come to the greenhouse all naked,

50:47.461 --> 50:49.380
"and the tomatoes turn red."

50:49.505 --> 50:51.632
Hang on!
The next week they meet again.

50:51.757 --> 50:53.842
"Well, did it Work?

50:54.635 --> 50:57.638
"Not with tomatoes,
but the cucumbers

50:57.763 --> 50:59.223
"are coming up like crazy!"

51:02.810 --> 51:06.230
<i>Once he was cussing
the mother of mine</i>

51:06.897 --> 51:10.693
<i>But I don't care about this
all, I'm not due for parole</i>

51:10.818 --> 51:13.737
<i>So I'm staying here
for a long while!</i>

51:13.862 --> 51:14.947
But I don't care!

51:15.072 --> 51:16.991
<i>I'm not due for parole</i>

51:17.116 --> 51:19.159
<i>So I'm staying here
for a long while!</i>

51:19.285 --> 51:20.619
Go quiet your child!

51:20.744 --> 51:22.329
That's yours!

51:22.454 --> 51:25.040
Don't you think I know
my own child's cry?

51:25.165 --> 51:28.252
Shut up, all of you!

51:28.377 --> 51:30.379
- They are all mine!
- Yes?

51:33.757 --> 51:38.012
"A retired soldier,
a spent bullet.

51:38.137 --> 51:40.139
"He is still a warrior,

51:40.264 --> 51:41.557
"It's a joy to be with him!"

51:42.016 --> 51:43.642
Here you are, my beauty!

51:44.268 --> 51:46.186
- Give me the pickle!
- Wait!

51:46.312 --> 51:48.856
Give me that pickle!

51:50.232 --> 51:52.443
Let's do it this way.

52:00.618 --> 52:02.202
One!

52:02.328 --> 52:03.370
Two!

52:03.495 --> 52:05.581
Three! Four!

52:05.706 --> 52:08.042
- Hello! Yes!
- Five! Six!

52:08.167 --> 52:09.835
- Coming!
- Seven!

52:09.960 --> 52:11.962
Eight! Nine!

52:12.087 --> 52:13.714
- Go there.
- Ten!

52:17.843 --> 52:20.471
Listen, she's a weirdo.
Doesn't talk, doesn't drink...

52:20.596 --> 52:23.098
Won't drink, won't smoke,
won't fuck your brains out!

52:24.975 --> 52:26.685
Get out of here.

52:30.606 --> 52:33.651
- There's a man looking for you.
- What kind of man?

52:33.776 --> 52:37.363
I told him about your problem.
He wants to have a look at you.

52:37.488 --> 52:40.824
Don't be afraid. I know him.
You can trust him.

52:40.949 --> 52:42.868
He's waiting outside.

53:02.554 --> 53:04.056
You're the one?

53:05.140 --> 53:06.266
Yes.

53:13.899 --> 53:15.275
Got your passport on you?

53:17.528 --> 53:19.613
Come on, give it to me.
Don't be afraid.

53:45.931 --> 53:48.892
OK. Let me see how I can place you.

53:49.393 --> 53:51.061
"Place" me?

53:51.687 --> 53:55.649
Relax. I'm just talking.

53:55.774 --> 53:57.234
Thinking aloud.

53:58.193 --> 54:00.112
What are your measurements?

54:00.654 --> 54:02.114
What measurements?

54:02.614 --> 54:06.410
Well, you know,
38-24-38 or something like that...

54:07.578 --> 54:09.121
I don't know.

54:09.246 --> 54:10.706
What for?

54:11.707 --> 54:13.667
For the record.
Don't know.

54:13.792 --> 54:15.627
The boss needs to know.

54:16.712 --> 54:18.464
What boss?

